Actor and presenter Thapelo Mokoena has revealed he would be starring in the third season of  UK series, Bulletproof. He shared the news on Instagram today, saying he would be starring with Ashley Walters, Noel Clarke and Vanessa Vanderpuye.Thapelo said he was grateful for this journey."It’s our time! I am incredibly grateful & proud to be part of this amazing UK series special. Im forever grateful for this incredible journey in the Arts. Mission Take Africa to the World is well in progress," part of his post read. BULLET PROOF 3 ?????????? • The cats out the bag. It’s our time! I am incredibly grateful & proud to be part of this amazing UK series special. • Im forever grateful for this incredible journey in the Arts. Mission Take Africa to the World is well in progress. • I’m starring on the biggest UK cop series along side @ashleywalters, @noelclarke & @vvbrownskin . An absolute honour. The BAD BOYS of the UK are in South Africa! • Thank you to the @skyone family & @vertigo_films for trusting me with this lead role. • This is Crazy! From our amazing #Trackers series opening on @hbo @cinemax in the USA & @zdfmediathek in Germany in a few weeks, to being on day 2 of filming the UK series, I’m just in awe. God I see You ???? • Clink in the link in bio to read up more about BULLETPROOF .Coming soon to a South African screens too???? • A big thank you to my @boss family for dressing my character on the show. No better fit ???? • The Power of Potential is in Process. A God Dream! #BulletProof #KeepMoving #KeepChasing #ThisIsAfrica #AfriCAN ????????????? A post shared by  Thapelo Mokoena (@mokoenalive) on Jan 13, 2020 at 12:30am PST 